Devious tech wizard Walter Mabry (Daniel Radcliffe) forces the infamous magicians to steal a powerful chip that can control all of the world's computers. Comment: For all of you who are wondering why they didn't call it 'Now You Don't' is because it took a long time to get the name Now You See Me recognized when it first came out. This has been said in multiple interviews that I have watched. ALSO, at the end of Now You See Me 2 it ends on a bit of a cliffhanger suggesting that there may be a third movie coming into the franchise therefore meaning that if they were to call this movie Now You Don't there wouldn't really be a suitable name for the next movie (presumably). ALSO, Isla Fisher (Henley Reeves) wasn't in the movie because when they were planning to film NYSM2  she fell pregnant resulting in her leaving the cast for this film. Thankyou.

Title: Now You See Me 2 Official Trailer #1 (2016) - Mark Ruffalo, Lizzy Caplan Movie HD
Comment: I saw this movie and loved it, as I did the first one. I hope that they make a third movie because the ending of this movie leaves a possibility for it. It depends how well, this movie does. The only disappointment for this movie is that you don't see the redhead, Henley from the first movie. It was planned for Henley to be in this movie but Isla Fisher was pregnant(with her third child) when they started filming so she was unable to reprise her role as Henley. So it was written that Henley left The Eye and a new female horseman named Lula, played by Lizzy Caplan, was selected by Dylan to replace Henley. If they make a third movie, perhaps they'll bring Henley back like maybe she'll want to return to The Eye. Though, I gotta admit, I liked Lula a lot, too!
